Silent Warrior:<br><br>
Looks like Pack Mom has some rowdy boys under her wing.  But if Cookie and Tom have to stand in the corner..then..I'll stand with them..that's where I belong..because I believe everything they say.  My silly posts could not stop them from engaging that &quot;design your own diploma, for a thousand bucks, expert.&quot;<br>
It is good that you are able to look at the stupidity that emanates from his sickness and just shake your head.  I salute you.  But, he has mastered a malipulative style..common to socio-paths &quot;Half Sweet talk + half bad mouth.&quot;  He is at once a fatalist and an opportunist.  He will become the weakest and cry the loudest over the shortage of water...but when water is found he will be the strongest in trampling the women and children to get the first drink.  That's the way &quot;IT&quot; is!<br>
Personally, I get a big charge out of his pompous fakery.  He entertains the academic judge within me.  I know the American Psychiatric Association does not endorse him.  I howl with delight at some of his stupid suppositions!  And now and then I step in to verbally kick his ignorant ass...sorry Mom..can't help myself.<br>
He does serve a purpose...Art divested a lot of anger on this &quot;pile of poodle dung&quot; and came away feeling better.  I don't like Tom getting flamed.  Tom, however has limits and they have been exceeded...Even Jesus cursed a worthless fig tree!<br>
All in all..it's good to see a skunk in the cross hairs..even if it does stink up the camp!<br><br>
MTF- the voice in Spatz's deaf ears..the mirror before his blind eyes...and the Cochran Boot up his hurting ass.<br><br>
Maka! hi yo po lo! Hiyo! Akicita Tanka doka la!  You can come out now, Skunk...the great warrior goes away!
